---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ChapterNav from "../components/ChapterNav.astro";
---

<Layout title="Database & Entity Framework Architecture - Abaki">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a
            href="/abaki-overview"
            class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to Abaki Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1
                    class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white"
                >
                    Database & Entity Framework Architecture
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Designing a relational database schema and implementing it
                    with Entity Framework Core
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        The database layer is the foundation of Abaki's data
                        persistence. Built with Entity Framework Core and
                        SQLite, it manages users, repositories, activities, API
                        keys, and code files. The schema design reflects careful
                        consideration of relationships, constraints, and future
                        scalability.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
                        Rather than relying on EF migrations alone, I designed
                        the schema intentionally, considering how entities
                        relate to each other and ensuring data integrity at the
                        database level.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Learning Journey
                    </h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                📊 Challenge 1: Schema Design
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                First time designing a relational database from
                                scratch. Learned to think about entity
                                relationships (one-to-many, many-to-many) and
                                when to use foreign keys vs. other patterns.
                                Initially made mistakes with circular
                                dependencies.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🔗 Challenge 2: Entity Relationships
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Understanding how to model relationships in EF
                                Core: navigation properties, foreign key
                                attributes, and cascade delete behavior. Had to
                                rethink some designs after running into issues
                                with orphaned records.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🔄 Challenge 3: Migrations
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Managing database migrations as the schema
                                evolved. Learned when to create new migrations
                                vs. when to squash them. Important for
                                maintaining a clean git history and deployment.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                📈 Challenge 4: Query Optimization
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Initially wrote inefficient queries that loaded
                                too much data. Learned about eager loading
                                (.Include()), lazy loading pitfalls, and query
                                projection (.Select()) for better performance.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                ✅ Key Learning
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Good database design saves countless hours of
                                debugging later. Time spent thinking about
                                relationships and constraints upfront prevents
                                data integrity issues downstream.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Key Code Implementation
                    </h2>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            User Entity with Constraints
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Model/User.cs
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.Schema;
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace Abaki.api.Model;

public class User
{
    [Key]
    [DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]
    public int Id { get; private set; }

    [Required]
    [StringLength(100)]
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required]
    public string Password { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; private set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;

    // Navigation property: One user can have many repositories
    public ICollection<Repo> Repos { get; set; } = new List<Repo>();
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Database-generated keys and timestamps prevent
                            manual manipulation. The navigation property allows
                            eager loading of related repositories.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Repository Entity with Foreign Keys
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Model/Repo.cs
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.Schema;
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace Abaki.api.Model;

public class Repo
{
    [Key]
    [DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]
    public int Id { get; private set; }

    [Required]
    [StringLength(200)]
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required]
    [StringLength(100)]
    public string Owner { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required]
    [StringLength(100)]
    public string RepositoryName { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required]
    public bool Watch { get; set; } = true;

    // Foreign key to AIAPIKey (nullable—can be set later)
    public int? KeyId { get; set; }

    [ForeignKey("KeyId")]
    public AIAPIKey? Key { get; set; }

    public bool WebhookActive { get; set; } = false;

    // Navigation properties for related entities
    public ICollection<Activity> Activities { get; set; } = new List<Activity>();
    public ICollection<RepoFile> Files { get; set; } = new List<RepoFile>();
    public RepoDefaults? Defaults { get; set; }

    [DatabaseGenerated(DatabaseGeneratedOption.Identity)]
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; private set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            The KeyId is nullable, allowing repositories to be
                            created without an API key initially. Navigation
                            properties enable efficient data loading via EF
                            includes.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            DbContext Configuration
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Data/AbakiDb.cs
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Abaki.api.Model;

namespace Abaki.api.Data;

public class AbakiDb : DbContext
{
    public AbakiDb(DbContextOptions<AbakiDb> options) : base(options) { }

    public DbSet<User> Users { get; set; }
    public DbSet<Repo> Repos { get; set; }
    public DbSet<Activity> Activities { get; set; }
    public DbSet<AIAPIKey> AIAPIKeys { get; set; }
    public DbSet<RepoFile> RepoFiles { get; set; }
    public DbSet<RepoDefaults> RepoDefaults { get; set; }

    protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
    {
        base.OnModelCreating(modelBuilder);

        // Ensure usernames are unique
        modelBuilder.Entity<User>()
            .HasIndex(u => u.Name)
            .IsUnique();

        // Cascade delete: when a repo is deleted, its activities are too
        modelBuilder.Entity<Activity>()
            .HasOne<Repo>()
            .WithMany(r => r.Activities)
            .HasForeignKey(a => a.RepoId)
            .OnDelete(DeleteBehavior.Cascade);

        // One-to-one: each repo has one RepoDefaults
        modelBuilder.Entity<RepoDefaults>()
            .HasOne<Repo>()
            .WithOne(r => r.Defaults)
            .HasForeignKey<RepoDefaults>(rd => rd.RepoId)
            .OnDelete(DeleteBehavior.Cascade);
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            OnModelCreating allows fluent configuration of
                            indexes, relationships, and delete behaviors.
                            Cascade delete ensures orphaned records aren't left
                            behind.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Efficient Data Queries
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// RepoService.cs - Query Patterns
// ❌ Bad: N+1 query problem
public async Task<List<RepoDto>> GetAllAsync()
{
    var repos = await _db.Repos.ToListAsync();
    // This loads all repos, then for each repo you access .Key, 
    // it triggers another query!
    return repos.Select(r => new RepoDto 
    { 
        Id = r.Id, 
        KeyId = r.Key?.Id  // Extra queries here!
    }).ToList();
}

// ✅ Good: Use Include for eager loading
public async Task<List<RepoDto>> GetAllAsync()
{
    var repos = await _db.Repos
        .Include(r => r.Key)      // Load related Key
        .Include(r => r.Activities) // Load activities
        .ToListAsync();
    
    return repos.Select(r => new RepoDto 
    { 
        Id = r.Id, 
        KeyId = r.Key?.Id
    }).ToList();
}

// ✅ Better: Use Select projection (only load needed fields)
public async Task<List<RepoDto>> GetAllAsync()
{
    return await _db.Repos
        .Select(r => new RepoDto
        {
            Id = r.Id,
            Name = r.Name,
            Owner = r.Owner,
            KeyId = r.Key!.Id
        })
        .ToListAsync();
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Include() prevents N+1 queries by loading
                            relationships upfront. Select() projections are even
                            better for performance when you don't need entire
                            entities.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Technology Stack
                    </h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {
                            [
                                "C#",
                                "Entity Framework Core",
                                "SQLite",
                                "Migrations",
                                "LINQ",
                                "Async/Await",
                                "Data Annotations",
                                "Fluent API",
                            ].map((tech) => (
                                <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                    {tech}
                                </span>
                            ))
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Results & Impact
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        The database architecture provides:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mt-3">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Data Integrity:</strong> Foreign keys and
                                constraints prevent invalid data states</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Efficient Queries:</strong> Proper indexing
                                and query patterns prevent performance issues</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Clean Code:</strong> Entity Framework abstracts
                                SQL, making data access code type-safe and readable</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Migration History:</strong> EF migrations
                                track all schema changes for reproducible deployments</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Scalability Ready:</strong> The schema can
                                grow without breaking existing code due to proper
                                abstraction</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
            <ChapterNav
                prevLink="/abaki-autofix"
                prevText="AI Auto-Fix Engine"
                nextLink="/abaki-encryption"
                nextText="API Key Encryption"
            />
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
